The paper deals with mechanism design and privacy, which are both topics in game theory (cs.GT). The concept of privacy is also closely related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of electronic polling and pricing of digital goods suggests a focus on computational complexity and algorithms (cs.CY, cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions a distribution of how agents value their privacy, which could involve information theory (cs.IT).
